Over 1.7 million U.S. students receive the Federal Pell Grant each year, yet an estimated $100 million in private scholarship funds go unclaimed annually, according to the National Scholarship Providers Association (NSPA, 2024). For the 2025–2026 academic year, the U.S. Department of Education reports that the Pell Grant maximum will be $7,395, but institutional and state-level scholarships often carry earlier deadlines—some as early as October 2024. Missing these cutoffs can cost you thousands in free aid. This guide compiles the firm deadlines for major U.S. college scholarships opening and closing in the 2025 cycle, including federal, state, institutional, and private programs. Data is drawn from the U.S. Department of Education (2024), the College Board (2024), and the National Association of Student Financial Aid Administrators (NASFAA, 2024). Whether you are a high school senior or a current college student, knowing the exact deadline window—not just the month—is the single most effective way to secure non-repayable funding.

## Federal Aid: FAFSA and Pell Grant Deadlines

The **Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA)** is the single most important financial aid form for U.S. college students. For the 2025–2026 award year, the **FAFSA** opened on October 1, 2024, and the federal deadline is June 30, 2026. However, state and institutional deadlines are often much earlier.

- **Federal Pell Grant**: Maximum award for 2025–2026 is $7,395. No separate application—eligibility is determined by FAFSA. Funds are limited, so filing as close to October 1 as possible is critical.
- **Federal Supplemental Educational Opportunity Grant (FSEOG)**: Up to $4,000 per year. Priority deadline aligns with FAFSA filing—many schools run out of FSEOG funds by March 2025.

State deadlines vary widely. For example, California’s Cal Grant requires a FAFSA submission by March 2, 2025, while Texas’s TEXAS Grant has a priority deadline of January 15, 2025. Check your state’s higher education agency site for exact dates.

## Institutional Merit Scholarships: Early Application Windows

Many four-year universities offer **merit-based scholarships** with deadlines that precede general admission. These awards are often the largest non-federal grants available to students.

- **University of Southern California (USC) Merit Scholarships**: Deadline December 1, 2024, for fall 2025 entry. Includes the Trustee Scholarship (full tuition) and Presidential Scholarship (half tuition). No separate application required for most programs.
- **University of Michigan Go Blue Guarantee**: Covers full tuition for in-state students with family income under $65,000. FAFSA deadline is March 31, 2025, but early submission by February 15 is recommended.
- **Boston University Trustee Scholarship**: Full-tuition award. Application deadline is December 1, 2024. Requires separate essay and recommendation letters.
- **University of Alabama Automatic Merit Scholarships**: Based on GPA and test scores. Priority deadline is December 15, 2024, for fall 2025. Awards range from $6,000 to full tuition.

